PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F442A1772474761
OL,3,CNatalie McNally murder accused claimer
OL,4,Cher ex-partner was 'abusive'
OL,6,FA man accused of murdering his
OL,7,Fpregnant girlfriend told police that
OL,8,Fher ex-boyfriend had been harassing
OL,9,Fher days before the attack in December
OL,10,F2022, a court has been told.
OL,12,FStephen McCullagh, who is accused of
OL,13,Fthe murder of Natalie McNally, made
OL,14,Fthe claim during a police interview.
OL,16,FMs McNally, 32, was stabbed at her
OL,17,Fhome in Silverwood Green, Lurgan, when
OL,18,Fshe was 15 weeks pregnant.
OL,20,FMcCullagh, 35, from Woodland Gardens,
OL,21,FLisburn, denies murder.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G1/12
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,443,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44202
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F442A1772474761
OL,3,CNatalie McNally murder accused claimer
OL,4,Cher ex-partner was 'abusive'
OL,6,FBelfast Crown Court heard on Monday
OL,7,Fthat he had indicated "no comment"
OL,8,Fmore than 80 times in his first
OL,9,Finterview with police on December 20
OL,10,F2022, after being arrested the night
OL,11,Fbefore for suspected involvement in
OL,12,Fthe murder of Ms McNally.
OL,14,FThe defendant, whose solicitor was
OL,15,Fpresent during the interview, was told
OL,16,Fthat he did not have to say anything
OL,17,Fbut that inferences could be made
OL,18,Fabout this at trial.
OL,26,@oD@WOUoD@bO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G2/12
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,443,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44203
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F442A1772474761
OL,3,CNatalie McNally murder accused claimer
OL,4,Cher ex-partner was 'abusive'
OL,6,FThe detective constable conducting the
OL,7,Finterview asked McCullagh about his
OL,8,Freply to the charge after being
OL,9,Farrested, which was: "Murder. Why?"
OL,11,FThe defendant said in interview that
OL,12,Fit was correct he said that.
OL,14,FAfter being told by his solicitor he
OL,15,Fdid not need to answer a question
OL,16,Fabout what he meant by that, the court
OL,17,Fheard he replied: "No comment."
OL,26,@qD@VOUqD@cO]yD@SOUyD@_O]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G3/12
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,443,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44204
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F442A1772474761
OL,3,CNatalie McNally murder accused claimer
OL,4,Cher ex-partner was 'abusive'
OL,6,FHe went on to tell police that he last
OL,7,Fsaw Ms McNally at 1pm on Sunday
OL,8,FDecember 18, when she left the house
OL,9,Fto return home for a shower before
OL,10,Fwatching a football match with her
OL,11,Fparents.
OL,13,FHe said the next time he saw her was
OL,14,Fon Monday night when he went to check
OL,15,Fup on her to see if she was OK.
OL,17,FHe told police he was her partner at
OL,18,Fthe time.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G4/12
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,443,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44205
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F442A1772474761
OL,3,CNatalie McNally murder accused claimer
OL,4,Cher ex-partner was 'abusive'
OL,6,FAsked to elaborate on the
OL,7,Frelationship, McCullagh said: "No
OL,8,Fcomment."
OL,10,FThe question and answers were detailed
OL,11,Fto the jury by a prosecuting barrister
OL,12,Fand the senior investigating officer
OL,13,Fin the case, who were reading from a
OL,14,Ftranscript of the interview.
OL,26,@oD@_OUpD@IO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G5/12
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,443,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44206
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F442A1772474761
OL,3,CNatalie McNally murder accused claimer
OL,4,Cher ex-partner was 'abusive'
OL,6,FThe court heard he answered "no
OL,7,Fcomment" to a range of questions about
OL,8,Ftheir relationship, his movements, his
OL,9,Fvehicle, Ms McNally's vehicle, his
OL,10,Fphone, the deceased's phone, her
OL,11,Fdiabetes, if he was on any medication,
OL,12,Fand if he had taken any alcohol on
OL,13,FDecember 19.
OL,15,FSome of the interview was read out
OL,16,Fverbatim while other sections were
OL,17,Fsummarised.
OL,19,FThe court heard more than 80 specific
OL,20,Finstances of McCullagh indicating no
OL,21,Fcomment.
OL,26,@nD@]OUoD@HO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G6/12
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,443,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44207
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F442A1772474761
OL,3,CNatalie McNally murder accused claimer
OL,4,Cher ex-partner was 'abusive'
OL,6,FHis solicitor told him he could answer
OL,7,Fa question about whether he was aware
OL,8,Fof any problems Ms McNally had with
OL,9,Fother people.
OL,11,FHe told the officer the ex-partner was
OL,12,F"harassing" her by repeatedly calling
OL,13,Fher phone and emailing her "a bunch of
OL,14,Fabuse". He described her ex as
OL,15,Faggressive and abusive.
OL,17,F"She was always very upset to hear
OL,18,Ffrom him,"
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G7/12
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,443,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44208
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F442A1772474761
OL,3,CNatalie McNally murder accused claimer
OL,4,Cher ex-partner was 'abusive'
OL,6,FHe said he had not met the man and
OL,7,Fadded that Ms McNally was upset when
OL,8,Fshe heard from him.
OL,10,FThe defendant said the emails were
OL,11,Faggressive and talked about her
OL,12,Fappearance in a derogatory fashion and
OL,13,Fused sectarian slurs.
OL,15,FHe said Ms McNally previously lived
OL,16,Fwith the man at her Silverwood address.
OL,18,FHe said he had no idea if there had
OL,19,Fbeen violence.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G8/12
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,443,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44209
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F442A1772474761
OL,3,CNatalie McNally murder accused claimer
OL,4,Cher ex-partner was 'abusive'
OL,6,FMcCullagh returned to providing no-
OL,7,Fcomment answers on further questioning
OL,8,Fabout what made him go to Ms McNally's
OL,9,Fhouse on Monday and his contact with
OL,10,Fpolice.
OL,12,FAsked if he had anything to do with
OL,13,Fthe death of Ms McNally, he initially
OL,14,Findicated no comment before the
OL,15,Fsolicitor said he could answer the
OL,16,Fquestion.
OL,18,FMr McCullagh then told police: "No."
OL,26,@zD@`OUzD@dO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G9/12
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,443,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44210
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F442A1772474761
OL,3,CNatalie McNally murder accused claimer
OL,4,Cher ex-partner was 'abusive'
OL,6,FHis solicitor said he was "very keen
OL,7,Fto co-operate as a witness" but argued
OL,8,Fhe was being treated as a suspect
OL,9,Fwhile it had not been confirmed there
OL,10,Fhad been an actual murder and there
OL,11,Fwas nothing to link his client to the
OL,12,Fincident.
OL,14,FThe court also heard evidence from a
OL,15,FPSNI detective constable about a text
OL,16,Ffile found on the defendant's computer
OL,17,Fwhich contained "Natalie timeline" in
OL,18,Fthe file name.
OL,26,@nD@[OUoD@[O]yD@QOUyD@bO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G10/12
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,443,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44211
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F442A1772474761
OL,3,CNatalie McNally murder accused claimer
OL,4,Cher ex-partner was 'abusive'
OL,6,FThe document appeared to have been
OL,7,Fcreated hours after the interview at
OL,8,F10.45pm on December 20, saved on
OL,9,FDecember 22, and had been most
OL,10,Frecently viewed on December 27.
OL,12,FIt said he had bought breakfast food
OL,13,Ffor the pair on December 18, and
OL,14,Fstarted drinking after she left to
OL,15,Fwatch football with her parents.
OL,17,FIt goes on to say he started a
OL,18,FChristmas Special livestream playing
OL,19,FGrand Theft Auto Vice City and Robot
OL,20,FWars from 6pm, in which he drank, and
OL,21,Fended just after midnight.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G11/12
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
